SYNCHT_CYCLES.Description: Pcycle stalls due to syncht instruction.

DU_UTLB_MISS_CYCLES.Description: Stalls due to misses in the D's uTLB.

CU_INTERLOCK_CYCLES.Hint_to_programmer: Schedule packets differently to avoid interlocks.

CU_BE_NOB2B_CYCLES.Description: CU Scheduler no dispatch due to no b2b interlock.

CU_EARLY_WRITE_CYCLES.Description: CU Scheduler no dispatch due to early write interlock.

CU_NOB2B_EXTENSION_CYCLES.Description: CU Scheduler no dispatch due to extension having no b2b restriction.

TOFF_CYCLES.Description: Cycles for this thread in off mode.

CU_RXX_INTERLOCK_CYCLES.Description: Interlock caused due to no b2b rxx network

POST_REPLAY_B2B_BLOCK.Description: CU scheduling penalty for du miss or du busy

IU_FETCH_CROSS_CYCLES.Description: Stalls due to jump target packet crossing 128 bit alignment.

IU_UTLB_MISS_CYCLES.Description: Stalls due miss in the I microTLB.

DU_FILL_CONFLICT_CYCLES.Description: Replay due to a fill in the dcache in the same cycle.

CU_BE_NOBSB_CYCLES.Description: Packet could not issued because previous packed was not a bsb type packet. Example NCJ.

CU_DU_XU_NO_FWD_CYCLES.Description: No B2B network between DU and XU

CU_FP_RX_NO_NTWK_CYCLES.Description: Interlock caused due to no FP->rxx network

ICACHE_DEMAND_MISS_CYCLES.Hint_to_programmer: Turn on prefetching. Use endloops instead of software loops. Use loop unroll.
ICACHE_DEMAND_MISS_CYCLES.Description: Cycles for the stall that event 18 creates. Each cycle, incrementes by the number of threads currently stalling on an I-cache miss.

CU_QOS_NODISPATCH_CYCLES.Description: CU Scheduler no dispatch due to qos

CU_DUAL_WRITE_INTERLOCK_CYCLES.Description: Cycles unable to commit due to packets dependent of results of dual write cannot go BSB or B2B.

DUNCACHED_DEMAND_MISS_CYCLES.Description: Cycles for the stalls due demand misses that are uncached.

DCACHE_DEMAND_LOAD_MISS_CYCLES.Description: Cycles for the stalls due to demand load misses.

FE_ISYNC.Description: Can't dispatch, waiting for cu_redirect after getting isync.

IU_HIT_STOP_ENDLOOP_TAKEN.Description: Fetch hole b/c taken endloop jump.

IU_HIT_STOP_PARTIAL.Description: Fetch hole b/c we encountered partial pkt.

IU_HIT_STOP_EOL.Description: Fetch hole b/c we fetched last packet in line and could not fetch further.

IU_HIT_STOP_RETURN.Description: Fetch hole b/c we encountered return jump.

CU_WRITE_PORT_BLOCK_CYCLES.Description: CU Scheduler no dispatch a non tc4x insts due to write port blocked by B2B tc4x inst, which must be on the same slot.

CU_WRITE_REG_BLOCK_CYCLES.Description: CU Scheduler no dispatch a non tc4x inst following a tc4x inst that write to the same register.

0x1.Name: COUNTER0_OVERFLOW
0x1.Description: Counter0 overflow. This can be used as the event detected by counter1 to build an effective 64-bit counter.

0x2.Name: COUNTER2_OVERFLOW
0x2.Description: Counter2 overflow. This can be used as the event detected by counter3 to build an effective 64-bit counter.

0x3.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_ANY
0x3.Description: Thread committed a pkt. Packets executed

0x4.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_BSB
0x4.Description: Packet committed 2 cycles after previous packet in same thread.

0x5.Name: COUNTER4_OVERFLOW
0x5.Description: Counter4 overflow. This can be used as the event detected by counter5 to build an effective 64-bit counter.

0x6.Name: COUNTER6_OVERFLOW
0x6.Description: Counter6 overflow. This can be used as the event detected by counter7 to build an effective 64-bit counter.

0x7.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_B2B
0x7.Description: Packet committed 1 cycle after previous packet in same thread.

0x8.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_SMT
0x8.Description: 2 packets committed in the same cycle.

0xa.Name: CYCLES_5_THREAD_RUNNING
0xa.Description: Processor cycles that exactly 5 thread is running. Running means not in wait or stop

0xb.Name: CYCLES_6_THREAD_RUNNING
0xb.Description: Processor cycles that exactly 6 thread is running. Running means not in wait or stop

0xc.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_T0
0xc.Description: Thread 0 committed a pkt. Packets executed

0xd.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_T1
0xd.Description: Thread 1 committed a pkt. Packets executed

0xe.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_T2
0xe.Description: Thread 2 committed a pkt. Packets executed

0xf.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_T3
0xf.Description: Thread 3 committed a pkt. Packets executed

0x12.Name: ICACHE_DEMAND_MISS
0x12.Description: Icache demand miss. Includes secondary miss.

0x13.Name: DCACHE_DEMAND_MISS
0x13.Description: Dcache cacheable demand primary or secondary miss. Includes dczero stall. Excludes uncacheables, prefetches, and no allocate store misses.

0x17.Name: CU_PKT_READY_NOT_DISPATCHED
0x17.Description: Packets that were ready at the CU scheduler but were not scheduled because (1) its thread was not picked or (2) an intercluster resource conflict

0x1c.Name: IU_L1S_ACCESS
0x1c.Description: IU L1S load. Demand or prefetch

0x1e.Name: IU_L1S_AXIS_STALL
0x1e.Description: IU L1S Stall due to AXI slave

0x1f.Name: IU_L1S_NO_GRANT
0x1f.Description: IU Request to L1S and no grant from VU

0x20.Name: ANY_IU_REPLAY
0x20.Description: Any IU stall other than icache miss. Includes jump register stall, fetchcross stall, itlb miss stall, etc. Excludes CU replay.

0x21.Name: ANY_DU_REPLAY
0x21.Description: Any DU replay. Bank conflict, store buffer full, etc. Excludes stalls due to cache misses.

0x23.Name: ISSUED_PACKETS
0x23.Description: Speculatively issued packets delivered from IU.

0x24.Name: LOOPCACHE_PACKETS
0x24.Description: Commmited packets which were cloned from the packet queue during a pinned hardware loop

0x25.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_1_THREAD_RUNNING
0x25.Description: Committed pkts with 1 thread running. Not in stop/wait

0x26.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_2_THREAD_RUNNING
0x26.Description: Committed pkts with 2 threads running. Not in stop/wait

0x27.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_3_THREAD_RUNNING
0x27.Description: Committed pkts with 3 threads running. Not in stop/wait

0x2a.Name: COMMITTED_INSTS
0x2a.Description: Committed instructions. Increments by up to 8 per cycle. Duplex counts as two instructions. Does not include endloops.

0x2b.Name: COMMITTED_TC1_INSTS
0x2b.Description: Committed tc1 class instructions. Increments by up to 8 per cycle. Duplex of two tc1 instructions counts as two tc1 instructions.

0x2c.Name: COMMITTED_PRIVATE_INSTS
0x2c.Description: Committed instructions that have per-cluster (private) execution resources. Increments by up to 8 per cycle. Duplex of two private instructions counts as two private instructions.

0x2f.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_4_THREAD_RUNNING
0x2f.Description: Committed pkts with 4 threads running. Not in stop/wait

0x30.Name: COMMITTED_LOADS
0x30.Description: Committed load instructions. Includes cached and uncached. Increments by 2 for dual loads. Excludes prefetches, memops, and coprocessor loads.

0x31.Name: COMMITTED_STORES
0x31.Description: Committed store instructions. Includes cached and uncached. Increments by 2 for dual stores. Excludes memops and coprocessor stores.

0x32.Name: COMMITTED_MEMOPS
0x32.Description: Committed memop instructions. Cached or uncached.

0x37.Name: COMMITTED_PROGRAM_FLOW_INSTS
0x37.Description: Committed pkt contains program flow inst. Includes cr jumps, endloop, j, jr, dealloc_return, system/trap, superset of event 56. Dual jumps count as two.

0x38.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_CHANGED_FLOW
0x38.Description: Committed pkt resulted in change-of-flow. Any taken jump. Includes endloop and dealloc_return.

0x39.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_ENDLOOP
0x39.Description: Committed pkt contains an endloop which was taken

0x3b.Name: CYCLES_1_THREAD_RUNNING
0x3b.Description: Processor cycles that exactly 1 thread is running. Running means not in wait or stop

0x3c.Name: CYCLES_2_THREAD_RUNNING
0x3c.Description: Processor cycles that exactly 2 threads are running. Running means not in wait or stop

0x3d.Name: CYCLES_3_THREAD_RUNNING
0x3d.Description: Processor cycles that exactly 3 threads are running. Running means not in wait or stop

0x3e.Name: CYCLES_4_THREAD_RUNNING
0x3e.Description: Processor cycles that exactly 4 threads are running. Running means not in wait or stop

0x3f.Name: AXI_LINE128_READ_REQUEST
0x3f.Description: 128-byte line read requests issued by primary AXI master

0x40.Name: AXI_READ_REQUEST
0x40.Description: All read requests issued by primary AXI master. Includes full line and partial line.

0x41.Name: AXI_LINE32_READ_REQUEST
0x41.Description: 32-byte line read requests issued by primary AXI master

0x42.Name: AXI_WRITE_REQUEST
0x42.Description: All write requests issued by primary AXI master. Includes full line and partial line.

0x43.Name: AXI_LINE32_WRITE_REQUEST
0x43.Description: 32-byte line write requests issued by primary AXI master, all bytes valid

0x44.Name: AHB_READ_REQUEST
0x44.Description: Read requests issued by AHB master

0x45.Name: AHB_WRITE_REQUEST
0x45.Description: Write requests issued by AHB master

0x46.Name: AXI_LINE128_WRITE_REQUEST
0x46.Description: 128-byte line write requests issued by primary AXI master, all bytes valid

0x49.Name: AXI2_READ_REQUEST
0x49.Description: All read requests issued by secondary AXI master. Includes full line and partial line.

0x4a.Name: AXI2_LINE32_READ_REQUEST
0x4a.Description: 32-byte line read requests issued by secondary AXI master

0x4b.Name: AXI2_WRITE_REQUEST
0x4b.Description: All write requests issued by secondary AXI master. Includes full line and partial line.

0x4c.Name: AXI2_LINE32_WRITE_REQUEST
0x4c.Description: 32-byte line Write requests issued by secondary AXI master

0x4d.Name: AXI2_CONGESTION
0x4d.Description: Secondary AXI command or data queue is full and an operation is stuck at the head of the secondary AXI master command queue.

0x50.Name: COMMITTED_FPS
0x50.Description: Committed floating point instructions. Increments by 2 for dual fp ops. Excludes conversions

0x51.Name: REDIRECT_BIMODAL_MISPREDICT
0x51.Description: Mispredict bimodal branch direction caused a control flow redirect.

0x52.Name: REDIRECT_TARGET_MISPREDICT
0x52.Description: Mispredict branch target caused a control flow redirect. Includes RAS mispredict. Excludes indirect jumps and calls other than JUMPR R31 returns. Excludes direction mispredicts.

0x53.Name: REDIRECT_LOOP_MISPREDICT
0x53.Description: Mispredict hardware loopend caused a control flow redirect.  Can only happen when the loop has relatively few packets and the loop count is 2 or less.

0x54.Name: REDIRECT_MISC
0x54.Description: Control flow redirect for a reason other than events 81, 82, and 83. Includes exceptions, traps, interrupts, non-R31 jumps, multiple initloops in flight, and others.

0x58.Name: JTLB_MISS
0x58.Description: Instruction or data address translation request missed in the JTLB.

0x5a.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_RETURN
0x5a.Description: Committed a return instruction. Includes canceled returns.

0x5b.Name: COMMITTED_PKT_INDIRECT_JUMP
0x5b.Description: Committed an indirect jump or call instruction. Includes canceled instructions. Does not include JUMPR R31 returns.

0x5c.Name: COMMITTED_BIMODAL_BRANCH_INSTS
0x5c.Description: Committed bimodal branch. Includes .old and .new. Increments by 2 for dual jumps.

0x5d.Name: BRANCH_QUEUE_FULL
0x5d.Description: Bimodal branch ignored. If queue is full.

0x5e.Name: DU_REQUESTED_BUBBLE_INSERTED
0x5e.Description: The number of bubbles CU inserted at the request of DU in an effort to avoid DU port conflicts.

0x5f.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_FIFO_FULL_CYCLES
0x5f.Description: Cycles cluster could issue scalar memory access to vtcm scalar fifo

0x66.Name: IU_LINE_FROM_HWLOOP
0x66.Description: IU line fetched from a detected hardware loop. Low power optimizations can elide various tag and data accesses here.

0x68.Name: IU_1_PKT_AVAILABLE_TO_ISSUE
0x68.Description: Fetch that could issue one packet independent of available packet queue entries.

0x69.Name: FETCHED_PACKETS_DROPPED
0x69.Description: Dropped packets because unable to deliver to CU.

0x6a.Name: IU_REQUESTS_TO_L2_REPLAYED
0x6a.Description: IU requests to L2 replayed. Could be IU and DU collision to L2 or IU credit failure. Could fire multiple times for a single transaction.

0x6b.Name: IU_PREFETCHES_SENT_TO_L2
0x6b.Description: IU prefetches sent to L2. Counts cachelines not dropped by L2. Excludes replayed prefetches and only counts ones L2 accepts.

0x6c.Name: ITLB_MISS
0x6c.Description: ITLB miss which goes to JTLB.

0x6d.Name: IU_2_PKT_AVAILABLE_TO_ISSUE
0x6d.Description: Fetch that could issue two packets independent of available packet queue entries.

0x6e.Name: IU_3_PKT_AVAILABLE_TO_ISSUE
0x6e.Description: Fetch that could issue three packets independent of available packet queue entries.

0x6f.Name: IU_REQUEST_STALLED
0x6f.Description: IU request stalled due to fill. Demand or prefetch fills from L2 to icache caused IU demand to stall.

0x70.Name: IU_BIMODAL_L2_ELIGIBLE
0x70.Description: This event counts the number of branches which resolved which can go to L2.

0x71.Name: IU_0_PKT_AVAILABLE_TO_ISSUE
0x71.Description: Fetch which could only issue a partial packet due to a jump to a packet which crosses cachelines boundary.

0x74.Name: IU_PREFETCHES_DROPPED
0x74.Description: IU prefetches aborted before accessing I$.

0x76.Name: L2_IU_ACCESS
0x76.Description: L2 cacheable access from IU. Any access to the L2 cache that was the result of an IU command, either demand or L1 prefetch access. Excludes any prefetch generated in the L2. Excludes L2Fetch, tcm accesses and uncacheables. Address must target primary AXI

0x77.Name: L2_IU_MISS
0x77.Description: L2 misses from IU. Of the events qualified by 0x76, the ones that resulted in an L2 miss (demand miss or L1 prefetch miss). A L2 miss is any condition that prevents the immediate return of data to the IU, excluding pipeline conflicts.

0x78.Name: L2_IU_PREFETCH_ACCESS
0x78.Description: Pre-fetch from the IU to L2. Any IU pre-fetch access sent to the L2 cache. Access must be L2 cacheable and target primary AXI. This does not include L2Fetch generated accesses.

0x79.Name: L2_IU_PREFETCH_MISS
0x79.Description: L2 prefetch from IU miss . Of the events qualified by 0x78, the ones that resulted in an L2 miss.

0x7a.Name: L2_IU_BRANCH_CACHE_WRITE_REQUEST
0x7a.Description: Requests sent from IU to the L2 to write the bimodal bits of instructions in L2. Includes all requests, without regard to target.

0x7b.Name: L2_IU_BRANCH_CACHE_WRITE
0x7b.Description: Writes to the bimodal bits of instructions in L2. This is the number of event 122 requests that completed by updating memory in the L2 cache or TCM.

0x7c.Name: L2_DU_READ_ACCESS
0x7c.Description: L2 cacheable read access from DU. Any read access from DU that may cause a lookup in the L2 cache. Includes loads, l1 prefetch, dcfetch. Excludes initial L2fetch command, uncacheables, tcm, and coprocessor loads. Must target AXI primary.

0x7d.Name: L2_DU_READ_MISS
0x7d.Description: L2 read miss from DU. Of the events qualified by 0x7C, any that resulted in L2 miss. i.e. the line was not previously allocated in the L2 cache and will be fetched from backing memory.

0x7e.Name: L2FETCH_ACCESS
0x7e.Description: L2fetch access from DU. Any access to the L2 cache from the L2 prefetch engine that was initiated by programing the L2Fetch engine. Includes only the cache inquire and fetch if not present commands.

0x7f.Name: L2FETCH_MISS
0x7f.Description: L2fetch miss from a programed inquiry. Of the events qualified by 0x7E, the ones that resulted in  L2 miss. i.e. the line was not previously allocated in the L2 cache and will be fetched from backing memory.

0x80.Name: L2_AXI_INTERLEAVE_DROP
0x80.Description: L2 drops a return or converts to uncacheable due to AXI interleave buffer overflow.

0x81.Name: L2_ACCESS
0x81.Description: All requests to the L2. Does not include internally generated accesses like L2Fetch, however the programing of the L2Fetch engine would be counted. Accesses target Odd or Even interleave, and may be L2 cacheable or TCM

0x82.Name: L2_PIPE_CONFLICT
0x82.Description: Request not taken by the L2 due to a pipe conflict. The conflict may be a tag bank, data bank, or other pipeline conflict.

0x83.Name: L2_TAG_ARRAY_CONFLICT
0x83.Description: Of the items in event 130, the ones caused by a conflict with the tag array

0x84.Name: AXI_RD_CONGESTION
0x84.Description: Primary AXI read command queue is full and an operation is stuck at the head of the primary AXI master command queue.

0x85.Name: AHB_CONGESTION
0x85.Description: Ahb congestion. Triggers when ahb interface is full and an operation is stuck at the head of the command queue.

0x86.Name: SNOOP_BLOCK
0x86.Description: Snoop block. Triggers when a snoop is not accepted and the snoop is blocking the head of the return fifo, and the return fifo has other items.

0x87.Name: TCM_DU_ACCESS
0x87.Description: TCM access from DU. DU access to the L2 tcm space. HVX requests are excluded

0x88.Name: TCM_DU_READ_ACCESS
0x88.Description: TCM read access from DU. DU read access to the L2 tcm space. HVX requests are excluded

0x89.Name: TCM_IU_ACCESS
0x89.Description: TCM access from IU. IU access to the L2 tcm space

0x8a.Name: L2_CASTOUT
0x8a.Description: L2 castout. Triggers when L2 evicts a dirty line due to an allocation. not triggered on cache ops.

0x8b.Name: L2_DU_STORE_ACCESS
0x8b.Description: L2 cacheable store access from DU. Any store access from DU that may cause a lookup in the L2 cache. Excludes cache ops, uncacheables, tcm, and coprocessor stores. Must target primary AXI

0x8c.Name: L2_DU_STORE_MISS
0x8c.Description: L2 miss from DU. Of the events qualified by 0x8B, the ones that resulted in a miss. Specifically the cases where the line is not in cache or a coalesce buffer

0x8d.Name: L2_DU_PREFETCH_ACCESS
0x8d.Description: L2 prefetch access from DU. Of the events qualified by 0x7C, the ones which are Dcfetch and dhwprefetch. These are L2 cacheable targeting AXI primary.

0x8e.Name: L2_DU_PREFETCH_MISS
0x8e.Description: L2 prefetch miss from DU. Of the events qualified by 0x8D, which ones missed the L2

0x8f.Name: L2_DU_RETURN_NOT_ACKED
0x8f.Description: L2 return to DU not acknowledged. This is active for any DU return, prefetch or demand. This event was renamed. I was called L2_DU_PREFETCH_NOT_ACKED

0x90.Name: L2_DU_LOAD_SECONDARY_MISS
0x90.Description: L2 load secondary miss from DU. Hit busy line in the scoreboard which prevented a return. Busy condition may include pipeline bubbles caused by back to back loads, as may be seen on L1UC loads.

0x92.Name: L2FETCH_COMMAND_KILLED
0x92.Description: L2fetch command killed because a stop command was issued. Increments once for each L2fetch commands that is killed. If multiple commands are queued to the L2Fetch engine, the kill of each one will be recorded

0x93.Name: L2FETCH_COMMAND_OVERWRITE
0x93.Description: L2fetch command overwrite. Kills old L2fetch and replaces with new one

0x94.Name: L2FETCH_ACCESS_CREDIT_FAIL
0x94.Description: L2fetch access couldn't get a credit. L2fetch blocked because missing L2fetch or L2evict credit

0x95.Name: AXI_SLAVE_READ_BUSY
0x95.Description: AXI slave read access hit a busy line

0x96.Name: AXI_SLAVE_WRITE_BUSY
0x96.Description: AXI slave write access hit a busy line

0x97.Name: L2_ACCESS_EVEN
0x97.Description: Of the events in 0x81, the number of accesses made to the even L2 cache.

0x98.Name: CLADE_HIGH_PRIO_L2_ACCESS
0x98.Description: IU or DU request for a high priority CLADE region. Not counted for L2 Fetch.

0x99.Name: CLADE_LOW_PRIO_L2_ACCESS
0x99.Description: IU or DU request for a low priority CLADE region. Not counted for L2 Fetch.

0x9a.Name: CLADE_HIGH_PRIO_L2_MISS
0x9a.Description: CLADE high priority L2 Access that missed in L2.

0x9b.Name: CLADE_LOW_PRIO_L2_MISS
0x9b.Description: CLADE low priority L2 Access that missed in L2.

0x9c.Name: CLADE_HIGH_PRIO_EXCEPTION
0x9c.Description: CLADE high priority decode that had an exception.

0x9d.Name: CLADE_LOW_PRIO_EXCEPTION
0x9d.Description: CLADE low priority decode that had an exception.

0x9e.Name: AXI2_SLAVE_READ_BUSY
0x9e.Description: AXI secondary slave read access hit a busy line

0x9f.Name: AXI2_SLAVE_WRITE_BUSY
0x9f.Description: AXI secondary slave write access hit a busy line

0xa0.Name: ANY_DU_STALL
0xa0.Description: Any DU stall. Increments once when the thread has any DU stall (dcache miss or dtlb miss).

0xa1.Name: DU_BANK_CONFLICT_REPLAY
0xa1.Description: DU bank conflict replay. Dual mem access to same bank but different lines.

0xa2.Name: DU_CREDIT_REPLAY
0xa2.Description: No. of time the packet took a replay because there were insufficient qos du credits available.

0xa3.Name: L2_FIFO_FULL_REPLAY
0xa3.Description: Counts L2 even/odd FIFO full replays.

0xa4.Name: DU_STORE_BUFFER_FULL_REPLAY
0xa4.Description: First packet puts access in DU store buffer (memop, store.new, load/store bank conflict, store/store bank conflict). Any later packet tries to use store buffer before the first one evicts, and so must replay so the store buffer can drain.

0xa5.Name: DU_STORE_BUFFER_FORCED_DRAIN
0xa5.Description: The number of times a store buffer underwent a forced drain

0xa6.Name: DU_SNOOP_CONFLICT_REPLAY
0xa6.Description: DU snoop conflict replay. Set-based match with stores inflight while a snoop comes in, and we replay the store. Snoop reads and writes the cache, needs to finish before the store can write. Excludes the fill replay case that a snoop can cause.

0xa7.Name: DU_SNOOP_REQUEST
0xa7.Description: DU snoop requests that were accepted

0xa8.Name: DU_FILL_REPLAY
0xa8.Description: A fill has a index conflict with an instruction from the same thread in pipeline. Fills and demands might be from different threads if there is a prefetch from the deferral queue or a fill has not be ack'ed for too long and forces itself in to the pipeline.

0xa9.Name: DU_SECMISS_REPLAY
0xa9.Description: A load hits on a reserved line while a fill is pending.

0xaa.Name: DU_SNOOP_REQUEST_CLEAN_HIT
0xaa.Description: DU snoop request clean hit. Snoop hitting a clean line

0xab.Name: DU_EVICTIONS_SENT_TO_L2
0xab.Description: Evictions sent by DU to L2

0xac.Name: DU_READ_TO_L2
0xac.Description: DU read to L2. Total of everything that brings data from L2. Includes prefeches (dcfetch and hwprefetch). Excludes coprocessor loads.

0xad.Name: DU_WRITE_TO_L2
0xad.Description: DU write to L2. Total of everything that is written out of DU to the L2 array. Includes dczeroa. Excludes dcclean, dccleaninv, tag writes, and coprocessor stores.

0xb3.Name: DTLB_MISS
0xb3.Description: DTLB miss which goes to JTLB. When both slots miss to different pages, increments by 2. When both slots miss to the same page, only counts S1, since S1 goes first and fills for S0.

0xb5.Name: DU_STORE_BUFFER_ACCESS
0xb5.Description: This event counts the no. of times an entry went to the store buffer.

0xb6.Name: STORE_BUFFER_HIT_REPLAY
0xb6.Description: Store buffer hit replay due to a packet with 2 stores going to the same bank but different cachelines, followed by a load from an address that was pushed into the store buffer.

0xb7.Name: STORE_BUFFER_FORCE_REPLAY
0xb7.Description: The store buffer must drain, forcing the current packet to replay. This usually happens on an cache index match between the current packet and store buffer. Could also a store buffer timeout.

0xba.Name: PORT_CONFLICT_REPLAY
0xba.Description: Counts all port conflict replays including the same cluster replays caused due to high priority fills and store buffer force drains, and intercluster ones as well.

0xbd.Name: PAGE_CROSS_REPLAY
0xbd.Description: Page cross replay. Page cross from valid packet that caused replay. Excludes pdkill packets. Counts twice if both slots cause a page cross.

0xbe.Name: DU_DEALLOC_SECURITY_REPLAY
0xbe.Description: Replays due to executing deallocframe or dealloc_return with FRAMEKEY != 0.

0xc0.Name: DU_MISC_REPLAY
0xc0.Description: All DU replays not counted by other replay events.  This event should count every time ANY_DU_REPLAY counts and no other DU replay event counts.

0xc3.Name: DCFETCH_COMMITTED
0xc3.Description: Dcfetch committed. Includes hit and dropped. Does not include convert-to-prefetches.

0xc4.Name: DCFETCH_HIT
0xc4.Description: Dcfetch hit in dcache. Includes hit valid or reserved line

0xc5.Name: DCFETCH_MISS
0xc5.Description: Dcfetch missed in L1. Counts the dcfetch issued to L2 FIFO.

0xc8.Name: DU_LOAD_UNCACHEABLE
0xc8.Description: Uncacheable load in L1 cache. Counts twice for dual uncachable loads.

0xc9.Name: DU_DUAL_LOAD_UNCACHEABLE
0xc9.Description: Dual uncacheable loads in L1 cache.

0xca.Name: DU_STORE_UNCACHEABLE
0xca.Description: Uncacheable store in L1 cache. Counts twice for dual uncachable stores. Excludes uncached memops.

0xcc.Name: MISS_TO_PREFETCH
0xcc.Description: Dcache miss is converted to a prefetch. Could be the second load to miss in a packet, or a DMT subsequent packet on same thread. The normal dcache access will proceed when the first miss resolves. Includes converted prefetches into uncacheable space which will be cancelled later in the pipe.

0xce.Name: AXI_LINE64_READ_REQUEST
0xce.Description: 64-byte line read requests issued by primary AXI master

0xcf.Name: AXI_LINE64_WRITE_REQUEST
0xcf.Description: 64-byte line write requests issued by primary AXI master. All bytes valid

0xd0.Name: AXI_WR_CONGESTION
0xd0.Description: Primary AXI write command or data queue is full and an operation is stuck at the head of the primary AXI master command queue.

0xd1.Name: AHB_8_READ_REQUEST
0xd1.Description: An 8 byte AHB read was made.

0xd2.Name: AXI_INCOMPLETE_WRITE_REQUEST
0xd2.Description: An L2 line-sized write was made to the primary AXI, but not all bytes were valid. This includes segmented writes. It excludes WT stores. The intent of this event is to capture the number of writes coalesced at a line level.

0xd3.Name: L2FETCH_COMMAND_PAGE_TERMINATION
0xd3.Description: L2fetch command terminated because it could not get a page translation from VA to PA. Includes termination dues to permission errors. i.e. address translation could fail because the VA to PA is not in the TLB, or the propertys in the translation are not acceptable and the command terminates.

0xd4.Name: REQUEST_STALL_WRITE_BUFFER_EXHAUSTION
0xd4.Description: Request to L2 stalled due to the lack of a write buffer. This is set for scalar and vectore stores.

0xd6.Name: L2_STORE_LINK
0xd6.Description: Counts the number of times a new store links to something else in the scoreboard.

0xd7.Name: L2_SCOREBOARD_70_PERCENT_FULL
0xd7.Description: Increments by 1 every cycle that the L2 scoreboard is at least 70% full. For a 32-entry scoreboard, this would mean 23 or more entries are consumed. This event continues to count even if the scoreboard is more than 80% full. For more than one interleave, this event only considers the scoreboard that has the most entries consumed.

0xd8.Name: L2_SCOREBOARD_80_PERCENT_FULL
0xd8.Description: Increments by 1 every cycle that the L2 scoreboard is at least 80% full. For a 32-entry scoreboard, this would mean 26 or more entries are consumed. This event continues to count even if the scoreboard is more than 90% full. For more than one interleave, this event only considers the scoreboard that has the most entries consumed.

0xd9.Name: L2_SCOREBOARD_90_PERCENT_FULL
0xd9.Description: Increments by 1 every cycle that the L2 scoreboard is at least 90% full. For a 32-entry scoreboard, this would mean 29 or more entries are consumed. For more than one interleave, this event only considers the scoreboard that has the most entries consumed.

0xda.Name: L2_SCOREBOARD_FULL_REJECT
0xda.Description: The L2 scoreboard is too full to accept a selector request and the selector has a request.

0xdb.Name: L2_DU_RETURN_REPLAYED
0xdb.Description: L2 return (demand or pre-fetch) replayed due to DU congestion.

0xdc.Name: L2_EVICTION_BUFFERS_FULL
0xdc.Description: Counts every cycle when all eviction buffers in any interleave are occupied.

0xdd.Name: AHB_MULTI_BEAT_READ_REQUEST
0xdd.Description: A 32 byte multi-beat  AHB read was made.

0xdf.Name: L2_DU_LOAD_SECONDARY_MISS_ON_SW_PREFETCH
0xdf.Description: Of the events in 0x90, the ones where the primary miss was a DCFETCH or L2FETCH.

0xe0.Name: L2FETCH_DROP
0xe0.Description: L2Fetch data dropped since prior eviction has not completed

0xe1.Name: REPLAY_MAXIMUM_FORCE
0xe1.Description: Maximum number of DU replays reached and this thread is forced through the DU by stalling the other threads

0xe2.Name: SCHEDULER_WATCHDOG_FORCE
0xe2.Description: Number of times the CU scheduler watchdog forced a threadpick.  This threadpick can be overriden by the livelock warning randomizer.

0xe3.Name: LIVELOCK_REFETCH
0xe3.Description: Number of times the livelock detector triggered a refetch of all threads

0xe4.Name: CYCLES_LIVELOCK_WARNING
0xe4.Description: Cycles core is randomizing scheduler due to passing livelock warning watermark. This could be a sign the core was not making forward progress, or simply that the watermark was set too low for legitimate stalls in the system.

0xe5.Name: THREAD_OFF_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xe5.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit due to thread off or wait.

0xe6.Name: ARCH_LOCK_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xe6.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit due to kernel lock or TLB lock.

0xe7.Name: REDIRECT_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xe7.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit due to redirects such as branch mispredict.

0xe8.Name: IU_NO_PKT_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xe8.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit due to IQ being empty.

0xe9.Name: DU_CACHE_MISS_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xe9.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit due to D-cache cacheable miss.

0xea.Name: DU_BUSY_OTHER_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xea.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit due to DU replay or DU bubble or DTLB miss.

0xeb.Name: CU_BUSY_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xeb.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit due to register interlock, register port conflict, bubbles due to timing class such as tc_3stall, no B2B HVX, or HVX FIFO full.

0xec.Name: SMT_DU_CONFLICT_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xec.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit because of DU resource conflict

0xed.Name: COPROC_BUSY_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xed.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit because of coprocessor busy

0xee.Name: DU_UNCACHED_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xee.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit due to D-cache uncacheable access.

0xef.Name: SYSTEM_BUSY_PVIEW_CYCLES
0xef.Description: Cycles cluster could not commit due to system level stalls including DMA synchronization, ETM full, Qtimer read not ready, AXI bus busy, and global cache op synchronization.

0xff.Name: VOLTAGE_CLOCK_GATING_CYCLES
0xff.Description: Cycles that core enabled voltage clock gating to mitigate a voltage droop event

0x101.Name: HVX_WAIT_EMPTY
0x101.Description: waiting context, qualified with cross-context VFIFO active

0x104.Name: HVX_REG_ORDER
0x104.Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode. Stall cycles due to interlocks

0x105.Name: HVX_LD_VTCM_OUTSTANDING
0x105.Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode. Stall cycles due to vtcm  load pending

0x106.Name: HVX_LD_L2_OUTSTANDING
0x106.Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode. Stall cycles due to load pending

0x107.Name: HVX_ST_VTCM_OUTSTANDING
0x107.Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode. Stall cycles due to store not yet allocated in L2

0x108.Name: HVX_ST_L2_OUTSTANDING
0x108.Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode. Stall cycles due to store not yet allocated in L2

0x10b.Name: HVX_ST_L2_SHARED_FULL
0x10b.Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode.  Insufficient space for data return to L2

0x10c.Name: HVX_ST_ST_BANK_CONFLICT
0x10c.Description: VFIFO stall due to VTCM ST bank conflict with ST

0x10e.Name: HVX_OTHER_PART_OUTSTANDING
0x10e.Description: Other part of the packet in another context not ready in 128 Byte mode

0x110.Name: HVX_VOLTAGE_UNDER
0x110.Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode. Throttling: Voltage model would exceed undershoot threshold

0x112.Name: HVX_PARTIAL_PKT
0x112.Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode. Stall cycles due to multi-issue packet

0x113.Name: HVX_PKT
0x113.Description: Increments by 2 per packet in 128-byte mode. Packets with HVX instructions

0x114.Name: HVX_ST_DWR_BANK_CONFLICT
0x114.Description: Store stall due to a DMA WR bank conflict

0x118.Name: HVX_PKT_THREAD
0x118.Description: Committed packets on a thread with the XE bit set, whether executed in Q6 or coprocessor

0x119.Name: HVX_CORE_VFIFO_FULL_STALL
0x119.Description: Number of cycles a thread had to stall due to VFIFO or SFIFO full

0x11a.Name: HVX_L2_STORE_ACCESS
0x11a.Description: L2 cacheable store access from HVX. Any store access from HVX that may cause a lookup in the L2 cache. Excludes cache ops, uncacheables, scalar stores

0x11b.Name: HVX_L2_STORE_MISS
0x11b.Description: L2 cacheable miss from HVX. Of the events qualified by 0xF9, the ones that resulted in a miss. Specifically the cases where the 64-byte-line address is not in the tag or a coalesce buffer. DCZero does not count as a miss, if it allocates without a backing store fetch

0x11c.Name: HVX_L2_LOAD_ACCESS
0x11c.Description: L2 cacheable load access from HVX. Any load access from HVX that may cause a lookup in the L2 cache. Excludes cache ops, uncacheables, scalars

0x11d.Name: HVX_L2_LOAD_MISS
0x11d.Description: L2 cacheable miss from HVX. Of the events qualified by 0xFB, the ones that resulted in a miss i.e. the 64-byte address was not previously allocated in the L2 tag array and data will be fetched from backing memory

0x11e.Name: HVX_L2_LOAD_SECONDARY_MISS
0x11e.Description: Of the events in 0xFB, the ones where the load could not be returned due to the immediatately prior access for the line being a pending load or pending L2Fetch

0x11f.Name: HVX_TCM_STORE_ACCESS
0x11f.Description: TCM store access for HVX. HVX store to the L2 tcm space

0x120.Name: HVX_TCM_LOAD_ACCESS
0x120.Description: TCM load access for HVX. HVX load from the L2 tcm space

0x12a.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_LD_GATH_ORDER
0x12a.Description: RAW hazard with older gather or release store

0x12b.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_LD_ST_ORDER
0x12b.Description: RAW hazard with older vector store

0x12f.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_LD_ST_BANK_CONFLICT
0x12f.Description: bank blocked by an older vector store

0x130.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_LD_LD_BANK_CONFLICT
0x130.Description: bank conflict with another vector load

0x133.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_LD_PKT
0x133.Description: Access and advance to next VFIFO entry

0x134.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_ST_PKT
0x134.Description: Access and advance to next VFIFO entry

0x135.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_SCATGATH_PKT
0x135.Description: Access and advance to next VFIFO entry

0x136.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_NULL_PKT
0x136.Description: Access and advance to next VFIFO entry

0x137.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_LD_DWR_BANK_CONFLICT
0x137.Description: VTCM Bank conflict with DMA Write

0x138.Name: VTCM_VECTOR_LD_DWR_ORDER
0x138.Description: VTCM Load is dependent with DMA Write

0x139.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_ACTIVE
0x139.Description: Any VTCM Scalar interleave not empty

0x13a.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_EMPTY
0x13a.Description: SFIFO empty, qualified with cross-interleave VTCM scalar active

0x13b.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_PORT_CONFLICT
0x13b.Description: Hazard port conflict with other interleave if any storeboards are occupied

0x13d.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_VECTOR_ORDER
0x13d.Description: Vector VTCM Scheduler not ordered with scalar access yet

0x13f.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_LD_SHARED_FULL
0x13f.Description: Insufficient space for data return to L2

0x140.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_BANK_CONFLICT
0x140.Description: Bank conflict with an older vector store

0x141.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_LD_PIPELINE_CONFLICT
0x141.Description: data return path to L2 occupied

0x142.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_BANDWIDTH_OVER
0x142.Description: VTCM per bank bandwidth for scalar will exceed the global bandwidth limit

0x143.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_LD
0x143.Description: Advance Scalar VTCM FIFO on load

0x144.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_LDHIT
0x144.Description: Advance Scalar VTCM FIFO on load hit

0x145.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_ST
0x145.Description: Advance Scalar VTCM FIFO on store

0x146.Name: VTCM_SCALAR_DWR
0x146.Description: Advance Scalar VTCM FIFO on DMA command write

0x148.Name: SCATGATH_SB_ACTIVE
0x148.Description: Any context scoreboard or the input buffer is not empty in a partition

0x149.Name: SCATGATH_SB_WAIT_EMPTY
0x149.Description: waiting context, qualified with cross-context network scoreboard active

0x14a.Name: SCATGATH_SB_EMPTY
0x14a.Description: selected context, qualified with cross-context network scoreboard active

0x14b.Name: SCATGATH_SB_WAIT
0x14b.Description: Transaction counting hardware in use by another context

0x150.Name: SCATGATH_IN_EMPTY
0x150.Description: Empty, qualified with any scatter/gather scoreboard not empty for partition

0x158.Name: HVX_VREG_RD_EARLY_WR_1PKT
0x158.Description: Vector operand read early with 1 cycle hazard

0x159.Name: HVX_VREG_RD_EARLY_WR_2PKT
0x159.Description: Vector operand read early with 2 cycle hazard

0x15a.Name: HVX_VREG_RD_EARLY_WR
0x15a.Description: Vector operand read early with no hazard

0x15b.Name: HVX_VREG_RD_LATE_WR_1PKT
0x15b.Description: Vector operand read late with 1 cycle hazard

0x15c.Name: HVX_VREG_RD_LATE_WR_2PKT
0x15c.Description: Vector operand read late with 2 cycle hazard

0x15d.Name: HVX_VREG_RD_LATE_WR
0x15d.Description: Vector operand read late with no hazard

0x15e.Name: HVX_VREG_WR_EARLY_WR_1PKT
0x15e.Description: Vector operand write early with 1 cycle hazard

0x15f.Name: HVX_VREG_WR_EARLY_WR_2PKT
0x15f.Description: Vector operand write early with 2 cycle hazard

0x160.Name: HVX_VREG_WR_EARLY_WR
0x160.Description: Vector operand write early with no hazard

0x161.Name: HVX_VREG_WR_LAT_WR_1PKT
0x161.Description: Vector operand write late with 1 cycle hazard

0x162.Name: HVX_VREG_WR_LATE_WR_2PKT
0x162.Description: Vector operand write late with 2 cycle hazard

0x163.Name: HVX_VREG_WR_LATE_WR
0x163.Description: Vector operand write late with no hazard

0x16a.Name: HVX_VREG_RD_EARLY_WR_3PKT
0x16a.Description: Vector operand read late with 3 cycle hazard

0x16b.Name: HVX_VREG_RD_LATE_WR_3PKT
0x16b.Description: Vector operand read late with 3 cycle hazard

0x16c.Name: HVX_VREG_WR_EARLY_WR_3PKT
0x16c.Description: Vector operand write late with 3 cycle hazard

0x16d.Name: HVX_VREG_WR_LATE_WR_3PKT
0x16d.Description: Vector operand write late with 3 cycle hazard

TOTAL_PCYCLES.Description: Total number of processor cycles to complete program.

COMMITTED_0_PKTS.Description: Number of cycles in which 0 packets were committed

COMMITTED_1_PKTS.Description: Number of cycles in which 1 packet was committed

CPP.Description: Overall Cycles Per Packet (CPP) for the core.

1T_CPP.Description: Cycle Per Packet when 1 thread is running

2T_CPP.Description: Cycle Per Packet when 2 threads are running

3T_CPP.Description: Cycle Per Packet when 3 threads are running

4T_CPP.Description: Cycle Per Packet when 4 threads are running

DFETCH_FILLED.Description: Number of dcfetch instructions which missed and filled the dcache

L2_CACHE_DU_DEMAND_MISS.Description: Number of Misses in L2 from DU requests (Demand only)

L2_CACHE_IU_DEMAND_MISS.Description: Number of Misses in L2 from IU requests (Demand only)

COMMITED_COMPLEX_ALU.Description: Number of non tc1 ALU instructions

AXI_WRITE_BYTES.Description: Number of total bytes written to the AXI bus (assumes 1beat transactions are 8B)

AXI_READ_BYTES.Description: Number of total bytes read from the AXI bus (assumes 1beat transactions are 8B)

HVX_LD_L2_OUTSTANDING.Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode. Stall cycles due to load pending
